&lt;p&gt;About Noble Machines&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Noble Machines (formerly Under Control Robotics, UCR) builds general-purpose robots that take on hazardous and physically demanding industrial tasks, enabling a safer, more efficient, and more productive world. Our work demands reliability, robustness, and readiness for the unexpected—on time, every time. We&#39;re assembling a mission-driven team focused on delivering real impact in heavy industry, from construction and mining to manufacturing and energy. If you&#39;re driven to build rugged, reliable products that solve real-world problems, we&#39;d love to talk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Position Overview&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Noble Machines, building robots is a team sport. As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Test Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will own the validation of our multipurpose humanoid robots across &lt;strong&gt;hardware, software, and AI systems&lt;/strong&gt;. You will operate the robot directly to stress test real-world performance, design and execute test plans, analyze logs and data, and produce clear reports that enable engineers to improve reliability and capability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on role focused on ensuring our robots are ready for deployment in demanding, production environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;e4a63a05 _037b10d8&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate humanoid robots to execute functional, stress, and edge-case tests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and run tests covering &lt;strong&gt;mechanical, electrical, software, and AI behavior&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate robot performance, safety, and reliability in lab and field environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document test procedures, results, failures, and observed behavior&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect and analyze logs, telemetry, video, and AI outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report clear, actionable findings to hardware, software, and AI engineers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify fixes and improvements through repeatable regression testing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;e4a63a05 _037b10d8&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience in robotics testing, systems testing, or hands-on technical roles&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating complex hardware or robotic systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to design structured tests and clearly document results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with testing or debugging &lt;strong&gt;hardware, software, and AI-driven systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working with logs, data, and basic analysis tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and clear written communication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work effectively in fast-paced, real-world environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nice to Have&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;e4a63a05 _037b10d8&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with humanoid, legged, or autonomous robots&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to AI or autonomy testing (perception, planning, control, or decision-making)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in mechanical, electrical, or software engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Field testing or deployment experience in industrial environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To apply, submit your resume here or email people@noblemachines.ai. We encourage candidates to include examples of hands-on testing, system validation, or field work demonstrating experience with complex robotic systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

